target.n.01.defn: a reference point to shoot at

prey.n.01.defn: a person who is the aim of an attack (especially a victim of ridicule or exploitation) by some hostile person or influence

target.n.03.defn: the location of the target that is to be hit

target.n.04.defn: sports equipment consisting of an object set up for a marksman or archer to aim at

expl: the sole object of her trip was to see her children
aim.n.02.defn: the goal intended to be attained (and which is believed to be attainable)

expl: it was replaced because of its age
we live in a litigious age
historic_period.n.01.defn: an era of history having some distinctive feature

expl: she was now of school age
age.n.03.defn: a time of life (usually defined in years) at which some particular qualification or power arises

expl: we've known each other for ages
I haven't been there for years and years
old age is not for sissies
age hasn't slowed him down at all

group.n.01.defn: any number of entities (members) considered as a unit

group.n.02.defn: (chemistry) two or more atoms bound together as a single unit and forming part of a molecule

group.n.03.defn: a set that is closed, associative, has an identity element and every element has an inverse
